description:

Just because they won’t call you, don’t mean they won’t sue you!

📧: you can send your money & credit questions to wwtmpd@themoneyplug.co (not .com)

When you operate in the spirit of service, announcing the things you’ve done can give you the ick, not gonna lie 😂😂 but (and I’ve said this a THOUSAND times) if Meredith Fineman didn’t teach me anything else from her book Brag Better, she taught me that your work can’t speak so you have to.

And keep doing it until other people are doing it on a live 24-hour news channel 🤌🏾✨

description:

description:
Won’t He do it?!

First, shoutout to @rahkimsabree for considering me for the article. I was so excited to share the Framework I created for financial service providers to ensure they are providing the help minority communities need, in a way that doesn’t further traumatize or shame them. And I’m featured alongside some of my faaaaaves! @millennialindebt (y’all know I love her book), @debtfreegonnabe (when it comes to student loans, that’s who I turn to), and @betterwallet (one of the inspirations behind me maxing my Roth contributions last year).

Comment LINK if you want a link to the article so you can read it for yourself! 🔗

Another shoutout to Dr. Soo, a professor at California State University’s Long Beach campus, who invited me to come speak to her class of future financial counselors on what this work looks like and what it took to get where I am now.

AAAAAND I MADE IT TO CLASS ON TIME 😂😂😂 my B in Spanish is safe!

All of this just a few days before my birthday trip to Mexico is truly refilling my cup in a way I didn’t know I needed.

Alexa, LET MY HATERS KNOW IM UP!

description:
👋🏾 Your financial counselor’s favorite financial counselor here✨

There’s 3️⃣ questions you should ask yourself when considering reaching out to one of us:

1. Am I consistently struggling to pay my bills on time and feel like my debt is out of control?

2. Do I have a clear and actionable financial plan for my future money goals? 

3. Am I constantly stressed or anxious about my financial situation, and is it impacting my quality of life?

If you answered yes to any of those questions, you should shoot me a DM or email! Even if you don’t want to work with me (I can admit I’m not everyone’s cup of tea 😅) As a member of the @afcpe, I have an extensive network of Counselor Cousins I can recommend to you! 

Have you ever considered working with a financial counselor?
